{
  "text": "As a running example, we use a version of the Asokan-Ginzboorg protocol [CITATION_1] for key agreement, also used in [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Let the set of players be {a i , i = 1, . . . , N } for N \u2265 1 and L be the leader. The protocol describes the establishment of a session key between the leader and the other N participants.",
  "correct_citation": {
